        "content": "<p>My preference is for the bulleted version, which doesn't bury important information in a large span of text as the paragraph-style one.</p>",
        "id": 1601992,
        "sender_full_name": "Karl Stolley",
        "timestamp": 1688140767
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, let's do the bulleted version, it feels a lot easier to skim. </p>\n<p>I think we might want the heading before the bullets to have a few more words explaining the connection, e.g. \"Archiving this stream will also disable settings that were configured to use this stream:\"</p>",
